ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiAbsoluteP.text: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiAbsoluteS.text: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiActive.text: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiAlwaysOnT.text: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiEnabled.text: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiExtentsOf.text: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiPlayerToH.text: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiStudsOffs.text: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiSizeOffse.text: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiSize.text: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.

ReflectionMetadata.BillboardGuiLightInfl.text: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceGui.text: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceGuiAdornee.text: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceGuiActive.text: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceGuiEnabled.text: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceGuiLightInflue.text: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiBase2dAbsolutePosi.text: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiBase2dAbsoluteSize.text: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

ReflectionMetadata.InputObject.text: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.

ReflectionMetadata.InputObjectUserInputT.text: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.

ReflectionMetadata.InputObjectUserInputS.text: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.

ReflectionMetadata.InputObjectPosition.text: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.

ReflectionMetadata.InputObjectKeyCode.text: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTweenPositio.text: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTweenSize.text: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTweenSizeAnd.text: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectActive.text: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectBackgroundCo.text: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectBackgroundTr.text: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectBorderColor3.text: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectBorderSizePi.text: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectClipsDescend.text: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectDraggable.text: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectSize.text: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectPosition.text: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectSizeConstrai.text: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectZIndex.text: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectSelectionIma.text: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectDragBegin.text: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectDragStopped.text: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectMouseEnter.text: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectMouseLeave.text: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectMouseMoved.text: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchTap.text: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchPinch.text: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchSwipe.text: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchLongPre.text: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchRotate.text: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectTouchPan.text: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectInputBegan.text: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectInputChanged.text: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiObjectInputEnded.text: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

ReflectionMetadata.Frame.text: A container object used to layout other GUI objects

ReflectionMetadata.FrameStyle.text: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameScrolli.text: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameCanvasS.text: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameCanvasP.text: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameAbsolut.text: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameScrollB.text: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameTopImag.text: The "Up" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "left" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameMidImag.text: The "Middle" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the "mid" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

ReflectionMetadata.ScrollingFrameBottomI.text: The "Down" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "right" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

ReflectionMetadata.ImageLabel.text: A GUI object containing an Image

ReflectionMetadata.ImageLabelImage.text: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info

ReflectionMetadata.ImageLabelScaleType.text: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

ReflectionMetadata.ImageLabelSliceCenter.text: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.

ReflectionMetadata.ImageLabelTileSize.text: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButton.text: A GUI button containing an Image

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButtonAutoButtonCo.text: Determines whether a button changes color automatically when reacting to mouse events.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButtonModal.text: Allows the mouse to be free in first person mode. If a button with this property set to true is visible, the mouse is 'free' in first person mode.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButtonStyle.text: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. More info

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButtonMouseButton1.text: Fired when the mouse is over the button, and the mouse down and up events fire without the mouse leaving the button.
Fired when the mouse button is pushed down on a button.
Fired when the mouse button is released on a button.

ReflectionMetadata.GuiButtonMouseButton2.text: This function currently does not work :(

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrame.text: A GUI that can show 3D objects

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrameImageTra.text: A number value that specifies how transparent the rendered image of the ViewportFrame is

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrameImageCol.text: The rendered image of the ViewportFrame will be multiplied by this color

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrameAmbient.text: Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the ViewportFrame.

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrameLightCol.text: Directional light color for objects in the ViewportFrame.

ReflectionMetadata.ViewportFrameLightDir.text: Light direction. Value will be normalized. All values valid except (0,0,0).

ReflectionMetadata.ImageButton.text: A GUI button containing an Image

ReflectionMetadata.ImageButtonImage.text: Specifies the asset id of the texture to display. More info

ReflectionMetadata.ImageButtonScaleType.text: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

ReflectionMetadata.ImageButtonSliceCente.text: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.

ReflectionMetadata.ImageButtonTileSize.text: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.

ReflectionMetadata.Handles.text: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable handles

ReflectionMetadata.ArcHandles.text: A 3D GUI object to represent draggable arc handles

ReflectionMetadata.SelectionBox.text: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object

ReflectionMetadata.SelectionSphere.text: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around an object

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceSelection.text: A 3D GUI object to represent the visible selection around a face of an object

ReflectionMetadata.Configuration.text: An object that can be placed under parts to hold Value objects that represent that part's configuration

ReflectionMetadata.HumanoidDescription.text: An object that specifies the appearance of Humanoid characters

ReflectionMetadata.Folder.text: An object that can be created to hold and organize objects

ReflectionMetadata.SelectionPartLasso.text: A visual line drawn representation between two part objects

ReflectionMetadata.SelectionPointLasso.text: A visual line drawn representation between two positions

ReflectionMetadata.PartPairLasso.text: A visual line drawn representation between two parts.

ReflectionMetadata.Pose.text: The pose of a joint relative to it's parent part in a keyframe

ReflectionMetadata.KeyframeMarker.text: Represents when an event should be fired in an animation

ReflectionMetadata.Animation.text: Represents a linked animation object, containing keyframes and poses.

ReflectionMetadata.AnimationTrack.text: Returned by a call to LoadAnimation. Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid.

ReflectionMetadata.AnimationController.text: Allows animations to be played on joints of the parent object.

ReflectionMetadata.CharacterMesh.text: Modifies the appearance of a body part.

ReflectionMetadata.Dialog.text: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players

ReflectionMetadata.DialogConversationDis.text: The maximum distance that the player's character can be from the dialog's parent in order to use the dialog.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogGoodbyeChoiceAc.text: Indicates whether or not an extra choice is available for the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogGoodbyeDialog.text: The prompt text for an extra choice that allows the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogInUse.text: Indicates whether or not the dialog is currently being used by one or more players.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogInitialPrompt.text: The chat message that is displayed to the player when they first activate the dialog.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogPurpose.text: Describes the purpose of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant icon on the dialog's activation button.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogTone.text: Describes the tone of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant color in the dialog interface.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogBehaviorType.text: Indicates how the dialog may be used by players. Use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer if only one player should interact with the dialog at a time, otherwise use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogGetCurrentPlaye.text: Returns an array of the players currently conversing with this dialog.

ReflectionMetadata.DialogChoice.text: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players

ReflectionMetadata.UnionOperation.text: A UnionOperation is a union of multiple parts

ReflectionMetadata.UnionOperationUsePart.text: Override the colors of the mesh with the part color.

ReflectionMetadata.NegateOperation.text: A NegateOperation can be used to create holes in other parts

ReflectionMetadata.NegateOperationUsePar.text: Override the colors of the mesh with the part color.

ReflectionMetadata.MeshPart.text: A MeshPart is a physically simulatable mesh

ReflectionMetadata.Terrain.text: Object representing a high performance bounded grid of static 4x4 parts

ReflectionMetadata.PointLight.text: Makes the parent part emit light in a spherical shape

ReflectionMetadata.SpotLight.text: Makes the parent part emit light in a conical shape

ReflectionMetadata.SurfaceLight.text: Makes the parent part emit light in a frustum shape from rectangle defined by part

ReflectionMetadata.RemoteFunction.text: Allow functions defined in one script to be called by another script across client/server boundary

ReflectionMetadata.RemoteEvent.text: Allow events defined in one script to be subscribed to by another script across client/server boundary

ReflectionMetadata.TerrainRegion.text: Object representing a snapshot of the region of terrain

ReflectionMetadata.ModuleScript.text: A script fragment. Only runs when another script uses require() on it.

ReflectionMetadata.ContextActionResultSi.text: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input event will stop at that function and no other bound actions under it will be invoked. This is the default behavior if 'functionToBind' does not return anything or yields in any way.

ReflectionMetadata.ContextActionResultPa.text: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the input event is considered to have not been handled by 'functionToBind' and will continue being passed to actions bound to the same input type.

ReflectionMetadata.SortOrder.text: The ordering to use for sorting an array of GuiObjects.

ReflectionMetadata.SortOrderName.text: Sort by alphabetical ordering of the Name property.

ReflectionMetadata.SortOrderLayoutOrder.text: Sort using the less than operator on the LayoutOrder property of GuiObject.

ReflectionMetadata.ZIndexBehavior.text: Controls the behavior of the ZIndex property.

ReflectionMetadata.ZIndexBehaviorGlobal.text: The ZIndex property will override the default value computed from the depth in the hierarchy.

ReflectionMetadata.ZIndexBehaviorSibling.text: The ZIndex property will control the order that the GuiObject will be rendered relative to its siblings.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleType.text: Controls how an image is displayed.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleTypeStretch.text: Force the image to fill the available space.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleTypeSlice.text: Use the SliceCenter property to stretch the middle of the image but maintain crisp borders.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleTypeTile.text: Tile the image using the TileSize property.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleTypeFit.text: Size the image to the largest size that will fit in the available space while maintaining aspect ratio.

ReflectionMetadata.ScaleTypeCrop.text: Fill the available space, maintaining aspect ratio by cropping the edges if necessary.

ReflectionMetadata.StandalonePluginScrip.text: A container instance that contains Scripts.  Useful only for Plugins.  When Studio starts, we load plugins into the 'UserPlugin' data model and execute Scripts contained in StandalonePluginScripts container. If a plugin doesn't have such a container then the plugin isn't loaded into UserPlugin data model.  When a data model for a place is created (e.g. the Edit data model), we load plugins into said data model and execute only those Scripts which are not contained in StandalonePluginScripts container.
